I don't think you understand the way modern recording technique works in the digital age. This song was not recorded in a studio with ten or twelve musicians playing the tracks live. It was recorded by her brother on a digital audio workstation. These songs are made vertically in layers, some of which are so subtle you need studio-quality headphones just to hear them. There are probably ten to twenty vocal tracks alone in this mix. Fans pay to see the performer and hear their music sound close to what they heard on the recorded version. So artists like Billie sing the lead vocal live over many backing tracks as she does here. She could travel with way more musicians, but it would still be difficult to recapture the sound fans expect to hear. This is both an artistic and a practical choice. Finneas has said that they did not want a large number of musicians on stage taking the focus away from Billie. I don't think there were many disappointed fans during her sold-out world tour with only three people on stage.

I've been a fan of Finneas for years and then i got into Billie when she started making music as well and although I've never met them or know them personally, i feel proud of them. Finneas is exactly my age (same birth month and year) and i feel extra happy knowing they're finally being recognized for the pure art they've been making for years. This specific performance always gets me teary eyed everytime i see it because Billie looks and sounds so free. It's heartbreaking that she genuinely had to go through all that she did but just to see the maturity, growth and self acceptance she embodies is beautiful and it's something not everyone chooses to do. She could have been petty (which in my opinion is impossible for her to be based on her life and relationship)  but even in the song she points this out. She hasn't implicated this douchebag into her narrative apart from merely stating what he did...She's focussed on herself and her journey by growing and healing and just being happy. And again, it would have been easier to follow this narrative that every artist now does where they trash their exes and it's so passive aggressive and just generally aggressive... but she did something so nuanced and matured and made it all hers: the pain, the beauty and everything in between and that is why this album deserved better. It was genuinely one of the best albums of 2021. Like Billie's, Twenty One Pilots, Kacey Musgraves, WILLOW and FINNEAS probably had the best albums of last year - FACT.
 I feel sad that it didn't get the awards it deserved and then i remember that Billie and Finneas are now in possession of half an EGOT. She didn't  need to worry about winning a Grammy that night because she won an Oscar and broke a few records while doing that 

And lastly, I tried so hard to not let my crush on Finneas grow bigger than it was. I thought i was over that (His time on Glee started it all those years ago) but then he decided to shred on guitar on top of a house and headbang. I'm done.
